# CODEOWNERS — protected-area review routing.
#
# Lines below are evaluated top-to-bottom; the LAST match wins per
# GitHub's CODEOWNERS semantics. A more specific path overrides a
# broader one, so we list the broad default first and tighten as we go.
#
# Maintainership disclosure (May 2026 audit HIGH-2)
# ===============================================
# This template is currently maintained by a SINGLE person (@DuqueOM).
# Adopters must understand the implications:
#
#   * Bus factor = 1: the entire governance surface (AGENTS.md, ADRs,
#     CI/CD, K8s, Terraform, security configs) is owned by one human.
#   * Environment Protection Rules in `templates/cicd/deploy-*.yml`
#     reference "1 reviewer (staging)" / "2 reviewers (production)".
#     With one CODEOWNER, the production-2-reviewer claim is aspirational
#     until a co-maintainer is onboarded. Adopters configuring their
#     fork SHOULD set `required_reviewers: 1` for production until
#     they add a second human, or accept that the second reviewer is
#     a peer-team handle (NOT this template's CODEOWNER).
#   * Single-person review concentrates risk for security-relevant
#     changes (`/SECURITY.md`, `/templates/k8s/policies/`,
#     `/.security-baselines/`, `/.github/workflows/`). Adopters with
#     compliance obligations (SOC 2 separation of duties, HIPAA,
#     financial services) MUST replace this CODEOWNERS with their own
#     team handles before treating the repo as governed.
#
# Path forward: open a PR adding a co-maintainer's handle to the most
# critical paths first (security, ADRs, CI). Track in
# `docs/decisions/ADR-024-multi-maintainer-onboarding.md` (TBD).

